    </a>
</div>
    <font size="4"><p>Your task will be to judge which of two methods did a better job of extracting an object.</p></font>


<div style="display: inline-block">
    <font color="black" size="6">How to compare two results?</font>
</div>

<div id="images">
    <a >
        <div id="container"><img src="intro_pics/ours_3.png" alt="Image" style="height:500px;" border="2"></div>
        <div class="caption"><b><font size="4">Result of method 1</font></b></div>
    </a>

    <a >
    <div id="container"><img src="intro_pics/knn_3.png" alt="Image" style="height:500px;" border="2"></div>
        <div class="caption"><b><font size="4">Result of method 2</font></b></div>
    </a>
</div>

<div>

    <font size="4"><p><b>1.</b> Pay attention to the <font color="red"><b>edges of the object</b></font>, areas like <font color="red"><b>hair</b></font> and <font color="red"><b>fur</b></font>, or any areas that are <font color="red"><b>semi-transparent</b></font>. </p></font>

    <font size="4"><p><b>2.</b> A bad result will have <font color="red"><b>smearing</b></font> or <font color="red"><b>chunky</b></font> artifacts, will be <font color="red"><b>missing pieces</b></font>, will <font color="red"><b>include pieces of the background</b></font>, or will <font color="red"><b>not look realistic</b></font>.  Do not worry if there is some discoloration.   </p></font>

    <font size="4"><p><b>3.</b> If you move your mouse over the image, you will see a close-up comparison of the images that will make it easier to judge the differences.</p></font>

    <font size="4"><p><b>4.</b> We show the same result on a white background and a black background to aid in seeing the differences.</p></font>

    <font size="4"><p>In the above images, method 1 is better than method 2.  Do you agree? Please contact <b>xn8812@gmail.com</b> for further questions.</p></font>

